25|$|In the United States, some Californian cities, e.g. Oakland and San Francisco, {{administer}} IRV {{elections on}} <b>voting</b> <b>machines,</b> with optical scanning machines recording preferences and software tallying the IRV algorithm {{as soon as}} ballots are tallied. Cary, North Carolina's pilot program in 2007 tallied first choices on optical scan equipment at the polls and then used a central hand-count for the IRV tally. Portland, Maine in 2011 used its usual <b>voting</b> <b>machines</b> to tally first choice at the polls, then a central scan with different equipment if an IRV tally was necessary.|$|E
