50|$|Security experts, such as Bruce Schneier, {{have demanded}} that <b>voting</b> <b>machine</b> source code should be {{publicly}} available for inspection. Others have also suggested publishing <b>voting</b> <b>machine</b> software under a free software license as {{is done in}} Australia. Software such as Sammaty come under GNU GPL, which means their source code is publicly available and hence transparent.|$|R
